# Aging reports parity (AP / AR / Owner AP)

Reports → **AP Aging**, Reports → **AR Aging**, and Owners → **AP Aging** (Owner AP) share the same UI patterns: columns, styles, Ref No links, totals, null property → **Company**, and drill-back through detail → summary.

## Mandatory sync

When changing layout, styles, columns, Ref No link behavior, back navigation, or detail/summary totaling on **AP Aging** or **AR Aging**, apply the same change to **Owner AP Aging** (same `ApAgingReportComponent` with owner mode, plus `buildOwnerApAging*` mapping helpers) unless the difference is intentional and documented here.

## Data sources (JE-based)

All three aging reports aggregate **journal entry lines**, not raw receipts/invoices:

| Report | Account scope | FIFO normal | Grouping |
|--------|---------------|-------------|----------|
| AP Aging | `defaultActPayableAccountId` (Accounting Office) | Credit-normal | vendor + property |
| AR Aging | `defaultActRcvableAccountId` (Accounting Office) | Debit-normal | contact + reservation |
| Owner AP | `defaultOwnActPayableAccountId` and/or chart **No 2001** | Credit-normal | owner + property |

Mapping helpers: `buildStandardApAging*`, `buildArAging*`, `buildOwnerApAging*` in `mapping.service.ts`.

## Do not change Owner AP behavior

Owner AP Aging is working and must stay unchanged unless the user explicitly requests it. When updating standard AP or AR aging, reuse Owner AP **UI patterns** only (layout, Ref No, drill-down shell)—do not modify `buildOwnerApAging*`, `loadOwnerApLines`, or owner-mode wiring in `ApAgingReportComponent`.

## Intentional Owner AP differences

- Includes **credits and debits**, and `IsCashOnly` entries (Owner Actual). GL / P&L / BS continue to omit cash-only via `JournalEntryLine_GetByCriteria` default.
- Ref No opens the JE supporting document via `sourceTypeId`/`sourceId` (and `RC*` / `R-*` code fallback), not only `receiptId`.
- Detail report title/scope copy may say Owner instead of Vendor.

## Ref No links

- AP, AR, and Owner AP → receipt, invoice, and **work order** (`WO*`) from JE `sourceTypeId`/`sourceId` (same blue underline affordance).
- Shell back must close embedded receipt/invoice/work order before leaving aging detail.
